**Step 1: Modify the proof of `h_R`**

We replace the proof of `h_R` to use `Fintype.card_sub_one_add_one` instead of `Fintype.card_eq_card_units_add_one`.

The line of thought is to use the standard result `|G| = |G \setminus \{0\}| + 1` which translates to `Fintype.card R = Fintype.card Rˣ + Fintype.card (unitsOfZero R)`. Since `unitsOfZero R` is the singleton `{0}` (as `R` is a division ring, so `0` is the only zero divisor), `Fintype.card (unitsOfZero R) = 1`. This gives `Fintype.card R = Fintype.card Rˣ + 1`, from which `Fintype.card Rˣ = Fintype.card R - 1 = q^n - 1` (since `h_card` states `Fintype.card R = q^n`).

```tactics
  have h_R : Fintype.card Rˣ = q ^ n - 1 := by
    have h3 : Fintype.card R = Fintype.card (Rˣ) + Fintype.card (unitsOfZero R) := by
      rw [Fintype.card_sub_one_add_one]
    have h4 : Fintype.card (unitsOfZero R) = 1 := by
      simp [unitsOfZero_eq_singleton_zero]
    rw [h_card, h3, h4]
    simp only [Fintype.card_ne_zero, add_tsub_cancel_right]
```

